It was Frank. He saw the baby.

01:04:14.100 --> 01:04:16.307
<i>- Are you sure it was him?</i>
- Yes, I'm sure.

01:04:17.420 --> 01:04:19.468
So that's why those Kluxers were here.

01:04:19.580 --> 01:04:21.503
Let me take him.

01:04:24.220 --> 01:04:26.143
Don't worry. I mean...

01:04:26.260 --> 01:04:30.982
if he's dumb enough to come back again, Grady
and the Alabama boys will take care of him.

01:04:32.060 --> 01:04:35.030
And if they don't,
I'll think of something.

01:04:35.140 --> 01:04:37.063
Don't take any chances.

01:04:37.180 --> 01:04:41.181
Promise me you won't do anything...
crazy, no matter what.

01:04:41.300 --> 01:04:43.223
Me?

01:04:43.340 --> 01:04:45.388
Not me.

01:04:46.900 --> 01:04:48.823
I'll go put him down.

01:04:50.540 --> 01:04:52.304
<i>Hey, little Buddy.</i>

01:04:52.780 --> 01:04:58.025
<i>That was the last anyone saw of
Frank Bennett until the night of the town follies.</i>

01:04:58.140 --> 01:05:01.667
<i>Ruth was away at one of
the Reverend Scroggins' many revivals.</i>

01:05:01.780 --> 01:05:05.068
One thing a woman expects
when she gets married...

01:05:05.180 --> 01:05:07.103
is sympathy.

01:05:07.220 --> 01:05:09.461
Haven't you got that since you married me?

01:05:09.580 --> 01:05:12.823
I sure have... from the whole town.

01:05:43.860 --> 01:05:45.862
Miss Idgie, you've got to come quick.

01:05:46.940 --> 01:05:48.863
But the show's hardly begun.

01:05:49.980 --> 01:05:52.586
You've got to come quick now, you hear me?

01:05:54.700 --> 01:05:58.421
<i>- Run and get help, quick!</i>
- Where's the baby? Never mind.

01:06:18.100 --> 01:06:19.625
Excuse me, sir.

01:06:20.740 --> 01:06:23.346
I don't believe you should be going anywhere

01:06:23.460 --> 01:06:24.985
with Ruth's baby.

01:07:10.540 --> 01:07:12.861
Hi there. What can I do for you boys?

01:07:12.980 --> 01:07:14.869
- Idgie.
- Grady.

01:07:14.980 --> 01:07:17.950
- This here is Sheriff Curtis Smoote.
- Hi there.

01:07:18.060 --> 01:07:21.109
He's over here from Georgia.
He's looking for a fella.

01:07:23.860 --> 01:07:25.783
- Do you recognise him?
- No.

01:07:25.900 --> 01:07:29.109
That's my husband,
but I haven't seen him in months.

01:07:30.180 --> 01:07:32.911
I heard he got run over
by a Brinks armoured truck.

01:07:33.020 --> 01:07:34.943
What's he done?

01:07:35.060 --> 01:07:38.348
Nothing that we know of.
We want to find out what's been did to him.

01:07:38.460 --> 01:07:43.261
He told his hired man he was coming over here
to see his wife and baby, but...

01:07:43.380 --> 01:07:45.303
he ain't never showed up back home.

01:07:47.300 --> 01:07:49.826
Hell, I told him if he showed up in this town,

01:07:49.940 --> 01:07:52.944
we'd all have known.
It looks a little sissified to me.

01:07:54.020 --> 01:07:58.230
From what I hear, most of you boys over there
in Georgia are a little light on your feet.

01:07:59.780 --> 01:08:01.703
That's the way I heard it.

01:08:02.900 --> 01:08:04.823
Could I interest you in some pie?

01:08:04.940 --> 01:08:07.750
No, ma'am, but that barbecue sure smells good.

01:08:08.820 --> 01:08:12.063
Best damn barbecue in the state of Alabama.

01:08:39.380 --> 01:08:41.303
Here you go.

01:08:41.420 --> 01:08:45.345
That's your fourth one today.
I swear you're about to eat up all my barbecue.

01:08:45.460 --> 01:08:47.383
Sit down.

01:08:52.620 --> 01:08:54.542
You ain't fooling me, girly girl.

01:08:54.660 --> 01:08:56.582
I know who you are.

01:08:56.700 --> 01:09:00.421
I heard from Bennett's hired hand
you threatened to kill Frank Bennett.

01:09:01.540 --> 01:09:03.542
<i>Now, he ain't showed up dead yet.</i>

01:09:03.660 --> 01:09:07.220
But if he does, you're in a whole mess of trouble.
You understand?

01:09:08.340 --> 01:09:10.581
<i>What we're talking about is murder here.</i>

01:09:10.700 --> 01:09:13.385
<i>Running afoul of the law, and don't nobody</i>

01:09:13.500 --> 01:09:16.822
get away with that,
not even a bunch of Alabama smart alecks.

01:09:18.700 --> 01:09:20.622
If I find so much as a hair of his head,

01:09:20.740 --> 01:09:23.265
I'll arrest you faster than you can slap a tick.

01:09:23.380 --> 01:09:25.667
<i>Cos I'm the law.</i>

01:09:25.779 --> 01:09:27.669
And you can't beat the law.

01:09:39.060 --> 01:09:41.506
You sure you ain't never seen this man before?

01:09:41.620 --> 01:09:44.749
<i>Yes, sir, I've already told you.
I ain't never seen him.</i>

01:09:44.859 --> 01:09:47.591
You'd do anything for Miss Idgie,
wouldn't you, boy?

01:09:49.340 --> 01:09:51.263
Yes, sir.

01:09:53.580 --> 01:09:55.503
Would you kill for her?

01:09:55.620 --> 01:09:57.827
Did you kill for her?

01:10:04.940 --> 01:10:06.942
No, sir.

01:10:07.060 --> 01:10:10.189
Well, now, maybe one of these days
you'll tell the truth.

01:10:14.140 --> 01:10:19.101
Just remember, we hang lying niggers
in Georgia just as fast as they do in Alabama.

01:10:19.220 --> 01:10:20.745
Yes, sir.

01:10:20.860 --> 01:10:22.783
I remember.

01:10:26.980 --> 01:10:30.268
♪ A God

01:10:31.380 --> 01:10:36.380
♪ To glorify

01:10:43.820 --> 01:10:46.346
♪ A never-dying soul to save

01:10:47.460 --> 01:10:51.385
♪ And fit it for the sky...

01:10:59.660 --> 01:11:01.583
Sorry.

01:11:02.700 --> 01:11:04.623
What are you doing in here?

01:11:04.740 --> 01:11:06.663
No milk in the house.

01:11:07.980 --> 01:11:09.948
Where were you?

01:11:10.060 --> 01:11:12.825
Taking care of business, having a good time.

01:11:14.940 --> 01:11:16.863
I've been thinking.

01:11:17.940 --> 01:11:21.308
Maybe I should move on,
because of Frank and all.

01:11:22.420 --> 01:11:24.343
I just...

01:11:24.460 --> 01:11:26.383
don't want you to feel like

01:11:26.500 --> 01:11:28.980
you have to look out for us.

01:11:29.100 --> 01:11:31.387
<i>I just...<i></i></i>

01:11:31.500 --> 01:11:33.502
don't want to be selfish, that's all.

01:11:33.620 --> 01:11:35.907
Maybe if I wasn't here you'd settle down.

01:11:37.020 --> 01:11:39.341
I'm as settled as I ever hope to be.

01:11:54.860 --> 01:11:57.750
Then... why can't you tell me where you were?

01:12:08.580 --> 01:12:11.504
I had a dream the other night.

01:12:11.620 --> 01:12:13.543
I dreamt that...

01:12:13.660 --> 01:12:15.583
Buddy was gone.

01:12:17.460 --> 01:12:20.987
I ran to his crib and there he was,
sleeping like an angel.

01:12:21.100 --> 01:12:26.391
And you know, I thanked God
for letting me still have Buddy.

01:12:27.500 --> 01:12:33.428
And I remembered having the same reaction
after Frank would beat me,

01:12:33.540 --> 01:12:36.589
thanking the Lord
for giving me the strength to take it.

01:12:36.700 --> 01:12:42.184
And I remembered... thanking the Lord
for each day that my mother lived.

01:12:44.300 --> 01:12:48.783
Even when she was spitting up blood
and praying for me to kill her.

01:12:50.860 --> 01:12:52.783
<i>I looked in my mother's eyes,</i>

01:12:52.900 --> 01:12:55.426
pleading for me to help her.

01:12:55.540 --> 01:12:58.464
And all I could do... was pray.

01:13:04.100 --> 01:13:06.023
While... While you were gone,

01:13:06.140 --> 01:13:08.063
as I was holding Buddy, I thought,

01:13:08.180 --> 01:13:13.744
"If that bastard Frank Bennett
ever tries to take my child,

01:13:15.740 --> 01:13:17.663
I won't pray.

01:13:19.460 --> 01:13:21.383
I'll break his neck."

01:13:24.780 --> 01:13:28.102
<i>Ruth, you don't have to worry
about Frank Bennett any more.</i>

01:13:29.220 --> 01:13:31.143
How can you say that?

01:13:31.260 --> 01:13:33.786
It's his child too. He won't give up on his blood.

01:13:35.100 --> 01:13:37.228
I'm only gonna tell you this one time.

01:13:39.580 --> 01:13:42.700
Frank Bennett won't be bothering you no more.

01:13:43.140 --> 01:13:45.063
<i>Understand?</i>

01:13:47.940 --> 01:13:49.863
You killed him...

01:13:50.980 --> 01:13:52.903
<i>...didn't you?</i>

01:13:53.020 --> 01:13:54.943
No.

01:14:02.500 --> 01:14:04.423
You don't believe me.

01:14:06.140 --> 01:14:08.825
Right now, I don't know what to believe.

01:14:11.180 --> 01:14:14.389
Believe me when I tell you
I don't want you to move out.

01:14:26.260 --> 01:14:29.662
♪ If I can help

01:14:30.780 --> 01:14:33.863
♪ Somebody

01:14:36.420 --> 01:14:38.866
♪ As I go...

01:14:38.980 --> 01:14:40.903
Finally.

01:14:41.020 --> 01:14:43.068
Thanks.

01:14:44.180 --> 01:14:46.103
I've been out here all day.

01:14:46.220 --> 01:14:48.143
♪ If I can show

01:14:49.260 --> 01:14:54.391
♪ Somebody

01:14:54.500 --> 01:14:57.982
♪ That they're travelling...

01:15:10.780 --> 01:15:12.703
Excuse me.

01:15:12.820 --> 01:15:15.664
- I was waiting for that space.
- Yeah? Tough!

01:15:15.780 --> 01:15:18.181
Face it, lady, we're younger and faster.

01:15:38.500 --> 01:15:40.423
Towanda.

01:15:56.740 --> 01:15:57.741
Towanda!

01:16:03.700 --> 01:16:05.623
Yes, ma'am!

01:16:13.380 --> 01:16:15.303
What are you doing?! Are you crazy?

01:16:15.420 --> 01:16:17.343
Face it, girls.

01:16:17.460 --> 01:16:20.111
I'm older and I have more insurance.

01:16:29.420 --> 01:16:31.661
I never get mad, Mrs. Threadgoode. Never.

01:16:31.780 --> 01:16:33.908
The way I was raised, it was bad manners.

01:16:34.020 --> 01:16:36.944
Well, I got mad and it felt terrific.

01:16:37.060 --> 01:16:40.064
I felt like I could beat the shit
out of all those punks.

01:16:40.180 --> 01:16:42.911
Excuse my language. Just beat 'em to a pulp.

01:16:43.020 --> 01:16:45.341
Beat 'em till they begged for mercy.

01:16:45.460 --> 01:16:47.383
Towanda the avenger.

01:16:47.500 --> 01:16:50.026
And after I wipe out all the punks of this world,

01:16:50.140 --> 01:16:54.589
I'll take on the wife-beaters like Frank Bennett
and machine-gun their genitals.

01:16:56.300 --> 01:16:58.223
Towanda will go on the rampage.

01:16:58.340 --> 01:17:03.267
I'll put tiny little bombs in Penthouse and Playboy
so they'll explode when you open them.

01:17:03.380 --> 01:17:07.942
And I'll ban all fashion models
who weigh less than 130 pounds.

01:17:09.060 --> 01:17:12.109
And I'll give half the military budget
to people over 65

01:17:12.220 --> 01:17:14.791
and declare wrinkles sexually desirable.

01:17:15.900 --> 01:17:19.700
Towanda, righter of wrongs,
queen beyond compare.

01:17:19.820 --> 01:17:22.426
How many of them hormones are you taking,
honey?

01:17:31.300 --> 01:17:36.181
♪ When you give more than you get
you're in danger...

01:17:36.300 --> 01:17:38.223
Well, honey,

01:17:38.340 --> 01:17:40.263
what I can't understand is,

01:17:40.380 --> 01:17:45.830
how in the hell you could hit someone
six times by accident.

01:17:45.940 --> 01:17:49.387
Oh, Ed. Don't make such a big deal about it.

01:17:55.580 --> 01:17:57.662
What the hell's this?

01:17:57.780 --> 01:17:59.703
That's a low-cholesterol meal.

01:17:59.820 --> 01:18:01.788
Happy Valentine's.

01:18:02.900 --> 01:18:04.868
♪ Heartbreak dead ahead...

01:18:04.980 --> 01:18:07.745
God! Are you trying to kill me?

01:18:07.860 --> 01:18:10.943
If I was gonna kill you, I'd use my hands.

01:18:11.060 --> 01:18:14.985
♪ Stop! In the name of love

01:18:15.100 --> 01:18:18.502
♪ Before you break my heart

01:18:18.620 --> 01:18:20.543
♪ Think it over

01:18:22.060 --> 01:18:23.983
♪ Think it over...

01:18:26.740 --> 01:18:29.061
I'm worried about my little friend Evelyn.

01:18:29.180 --> 01:18:34.505
She said her husband Ed would just be
sitting around watching his sports on TV,

01:18:34.620 --> 01:18:37.863
and she has an urge to hit him in the head
with a baseball bat.

01:18:37.980 --> 01:18:39.903
Hell, that seems normal to me.

01:18:40.020 --> 01:18:41.943
Hi, Janeen.

01:18:42.060 --> 01:18:44.984
Hi, Mrs. Threadgoode.
Would you like some crudités?

01:18:45.100 --> 01:18:48.422
Thank you, Evelyn,
but this raw stuff don't sit good with me.

01:18:49.540 --> 01:18:52.271
Mrs. Threadgoode,
you have to tell me something.

01:18:53.380 --> 01:18:55.428
Did Idgie murder Frank Bennett or not?

01:18:55.540 --> 01:18:57.463
Well, hold your horses, honey.

01:18:57.580 --> 01:18:59.503
Where were we?

01:19:01.020 --> 01:19:02.943
You didn't kill Ed, now, did you?

01:19:03.060 --> 01:19:04.983
Not yet.

01:19:05.100 --> 01:19:07.068
Oh, good.

01:19:07.180 --> 01:19:11.629
Anyway, five years had passed
since Frank Bennett disappeared.

01:19:11.740 --> 01:19:16.189
<i>And Smokey Lonesome had been missing
ever since that same terrible night</i>

01:19:16.300 --> 01:19:18.621
<i>I remember the day when he showed up again.</i>

01:19:19.740 --> 01:19:21.663
By God, son,

01:19:21.780 --> 01:19:24.101
you're the spitting image of Ruth.

01:19:24.220 --> 01:19:26.951
Buddy Threadgoode Junior.
Nice to meet you, sir.

01:19:27.060 --> 01:19:29.745
Well, sir, Smokey Lonesome.

01:19:29.860 --> 01:19:32.864
<i>Curtis Smoote was making
one of his visits to Whistle Stop,</i>

01:19:32.980 --> 01:19:38.589
<i>still hunting and pecking for any scrap
of evidence about Frank Bennett's whereabouts.</i>

01:19:38.700 --> 01:19:41.021
<i>- Who wants to begin?
- I do!</i>

01:19:41.140 --> 01:19:42.869
- I do, Miss Ruth.
<i>- Thank you.</i>

01:19:43.980 --> 01:19:45.903
We'll begin on page five.

01:19:46.020 --> 01:19:48.261
<i>Life has a funny way of working things out.</i>

01:19:49.380 --> 01:19:51.109
Well, hey there!

01:19:51.220 --> 01:19:53.143
<i>Smokey!</i>

01:19:53.260 --> 01:19:54.591
Idgie?

01:19:54.700 --> 01:19:58.022
Smokey Lonesome.
Well, if it isn't old home week!

01:19:58.140 --> 01:20:01.587
<i>- How are you?</i>
- Well, I'm rattling but I'm rolling.

01:20:01.700 --> 01:20:03.589
What brings you to these pans?

01:20:03.700 --> 01:20:06.670
- The smell of good cooking.
- Hey, Smokey.

01:20:07.780 --> 01:20:09.703
Let me fix you some lunch.

01:20:09.820 --> 01:20:13.950
I think you know just about everybody
except maybe Curtis Smoote.

01:20:14.060 --> 01:20:15.903
<i>He's an officer from Valdosta, Georgia.</i>

01:20:16.020 --> 01:20:21.390
He's been looking for the same man
for almost five years. A very stubborn fellow!

01:20:21.500 --> 01:20:23.423
<i>He loves our barbecue.</i>

01:20:24.500 --> 01:20:26.104
<i>Mommy!</i>

01:20:26.220 --> 01:20:28.063
<i>Mommy, help!</i>

01:20:34.460 --> 01:20:36.269
Buddy!

01:20:36.380 --> 01:20:38.303
Everybody out of the way.

01:20:38.420 --> 01:20:40.343
Let me in. Give him here.

01:20:40.460 --> 01:20:41.825
Let him go.

01:20:41.940 --> 01:20:43.863
I got him.

01:20:44.980 --> 01:20:47.062
He's gonna be all right. Open the door!

01:20:48.140 --> 01:20:50.063
Put him in the back.

01:20:50.180 --> 01:20:52.148
Get him in the car. It's all right, honey.

01:21:14.460 --> 01:21:16.861
I can understand having a funeral for an arm.

01:21:16.980 --> 01:21:20.268
I just don't know why I should insist
on calling him Stump.

01:21:20.380 --> 01:21:23.224
<i>She said everybody else
gonna be calling him that</i>

01:21:23.340 --> 01:21:25.661
So we might just as well be the first.

01:21:27.340 --> 01:21:30.549
<i>OK, ice cream and cakes for everybody
in the café.</i>

01:21:37.420 --> 01:21:41.061
My daddy always used to say
there was a separate God for children.

01:21:44.180 --> 01:21:46.831
<i>The good Lord
was watching over Stump that day.</i>

01:21:48.300 --> 01:21:50.462
<i>But then it started to rain that month.</i>

01:21:51.580 --> 01:21:55.221
<i>And it rained and it rained,
and it flooded parts of Whistle Stop.</i>

01:21:55.340 --> 01:21:59.425
<i>And that's why Grady's deputy stumbled
onto Frank Bennett's pick-up truck.</i>

01:22:00.900 --> 01:22:02.823
<i>And I just knew</i>

01:22:02.940 --> 01:22:05.068
<i>Idgie would never get out of this mess.</i>

01:22:05.180 --> 01:22:07.103
Now, are you in or out?

01:22:07.220 --> 01:22:10.747
- Remember, Ruth, I didn't take any cards.
- Let me see your face.

01:22:10.860 --> 01:22:13.511
- Idgie, I have to talk to you.
- You're bluffing.

01:22:13.620 --> 01:22:16.829
Grady, sit in, I'll deal you a new hand.
Gladys won't mind.

01:22:16.940 --> 01:22:18.863
In private, Idgie.

01:22:18.980 --> 01:22:20.903
Excuse us, Ruth.

01:22:22.820 --> 01:22:25.824
I'm just trying to teach you
not to fall for any tricks.

01:22:25.940 --> 01:22:27.863
You're doing a great job.

01:22:37.260 --> 01:22:39.183
What's your hurry?

01:22:39.300 --> 01:22:41.223
What is so important?

01:22:42.860 --> 01:22:44.783
What's that?

01:22:44.900 --> 01:22:48.063
<i>Somebody found Frank Bennett's truck
in the river.</i>

01:22:49.220 --> 01:22:51.143
What's that got to do with me?

01:22:51.260 --> 01:22:54.901
Well, officially, you and Big George
are under arrest for murder.

01:22:55.020 --> 01:22:57.022
You're in my custody until tomorrow.

01:22:57.140 --> 01:23:00.542
I'm supposed to take you over to Georgia
first thing in the morning.

01:23:01.660 --> 01:23:03.583
<i>Unless, of course...</i>

01:23:04.740 --> 01:23:09.462
Well, some people have been known to pack up
and sneak out of town in the middle of the night.

01:23:13.300 --> 01:23:15.746
<i>What about Big George?</i>

01:23:16.860 --> 01:23:20.307
Well, the way I figure it,
they'd be satisfied if they had him.

01:23:21.420 --> 01:23:23.343
Idgie, this is serious.

01:23:23.460 --> 01:23:25.383
We're talking murder of a white man.

01:23:25.500 --> 01:23:27.423
Someone's gonna have to pay.

01:23:28.540 --> 01:23:30.463
Nobody wants to hang a woman.

01:23:31.940 --> 01:23:33.863
No deal.

01:23:34.980 --> 01:23:38.189
Idgie, I know how you feel about Big George.
Hell, we all do.

01:23:39.300 --> 01:23:41.223
But these are just the facts of life.

01:23:44.300 --> 01:23:46.223
I can't do that.

01:23:46.340 --> 01:23:48.468
Take me to jail if you have to.

01:23:49.580 --> 01:23:52.026
Well, that's what I thought you'd say!

01:23:52.140 --> 01:23:54.381
You are absolutely, unconditionally,

01:23:54.500 --> 01:23:58.744
positively the most stubborn person
I've ever known in my life!

01:24:00.260 --> 01:24:03.469
<i>So Idgie and Big George
went to the county jail</i>

01:24:03.580 --> 01:24:07.141
<i>in Valdosta, to await trial
for the murder of Frank Bennett.</i>

01:24:08.460 --> 01:24:10.383
<i>They didn't have to wait too long.</i>

01:24:10.500 --> 01:24:12.423
Did you know Frank Bennett?

01:24:12.540 --> 01:24:14.269
No, sir.

01:24:14.380 --> 01:24:18.908
You mean to tell me you never met the man
whose wife, Ruth, is your business partner?

01:24:19.020 --> 01:24:20.943
<i>That's right.</i>

01:24:21.060 --> 01:24:27.147
You never threatened to kill Frank Bennett, at his
home in front of his hired man, in June 1932,

01:24:27.260 --> 01:24:29.388
the same Frank Bennett you did not know?

01:24:29.500 --> 01:24:31.423
<i>Oh, that was me, all right.</i>

01:24:31.540 --> 01:24:33.986
<i>I thought you wanted to know if we'd ever met.</i>

01:24:34.100 --> 01:24:36.023
<i>The answer's no.</i>

01:24:36.140 --> 01:24:41.863
<i>I threatened to kill him, but we were never
what you might say, properly introduced.</i>

01:24:41.980 --> 01:24:45.905
Is it not true that in September of 1932,
you came to Valdosta

01:24:46.020 --> 01:24:49.661
<i>and took Frank Bennett's wife and child
back to Alabama with you?</i>

01:24:49.780 --> 01:24:51.703
Just the wife. The child came later.

01:24:51.820 --> 01:24:53.424
How much later?

01:24:53.540 --> 01:24:55.463
The usual. Nine months.

01:24:55.580 --> 01:24:58.265
<i>Well, I suggest</i>

01:24:58.380 --> 01:25:03.261
that you bribed this poor weak woman
with promises of liquor and money

01:25:03.380 --> 01:25:06.782
and she lost control of her senses momentarily.

01:25:06.900 --> 01:25:10.029
And when her husband came back to get her
and take her home,

01:25:10.140 --> 01:25:14.589
you and your coloured man
murdered him in cold blood.

01:25:15.700 --> 01:25:17.270
No, sir.

01:25:17.380 --> 01:25:21.988
Well, where were you on the night of
September 30th, 1933?

01:25:22.100 --> 01:25:24.023
I was at the town hall doing a show.

01:25:24.140 --> 01:25:27.667
- And after that?
- I was over at my mother's house.

01:25:27.780 --> 01:25:29.703
Oh, yeah? Who was with you?

01:25:29.820 --> 01:25:31.743
<i>Just Big George and myself.</i>

01:25:31.860 --> 01:25:34.386
What about your mother? Can she confirm that?

01:25:34.500 --> 01:25:36.662
No, sir. She died a year ago.

01:25:36.780 --> 01:25:41.991
I'm sorry to hear that. But, Miss Threadgoode,
do you expect 12 intelligent men to believe you,

01:25:42.100 --> 01:25:45.343
although one witness is dead
and the other is a coloured man

01:25:45.460 --> 01:25:48.066
known to be a worthless, no-good, lying nigger?

01:25:48.180 --> 01:25:50.945
You expect these men to take your word for it

01:25:51.060 --> 01:25:53.381
<i>just because you say so?</i>

01:25:53.500 --> 01:25:57.300
That's right, you gump-faced, blown-up,
baboon-assed bastard!

01:25:59.460 --> 01:26:01.383
<i>One more outburst like that,</i>

01:26:01.500 --> 01:26:04.788
and I'll hold you in contempt of court,
do you understand?

01:26:04.900 --> 01:26:06.550
Yes, sir.

01:26:07.660 --> 01:26:09.583
Lord!

01:26:10.700 --> 01:26:12.623
Next witness, please.

01:26:14.900 --> 01:26:18.700
<i>Did you know that you were pregnant
at the time you left Valdosta?</i>

01:26:18.820 --> 01:26:20.743
<i>Yes.</i>

01:26:20.860 --> 01:26:29.223
<i>And yet you tell us over and over
that you went with this woman willingly.</i>

01:26:29.340 --> 01:26:33.061
Yes, I wouldn't raise my child with Frank Bennett.

01:26:33.180 --> 01:26:35.103
<i>But Why?</i>

01:26:35.220 --> 01:26:37.541
<i>Did this woman promise you money?</i>

01:26:37.660 --> 01:26:39.583
No.

01:26:39.700 --> 01:26:41.623
<i>A bigger home?</i>

01:26:41.740 --> 01:26:44.664
No... no.

01:26:44.780 --> 01:26:46.703
<i>Then tell us, Mrs. Bennett,</i>

01:26:46.820 --> 01:26:51.462
<i>why would a respectable Christian woman
go anywhere with this Idgie Threadgoode,</i>

01:26:51.580 --> 01:26:54.789
<i>- whose reputation is known far and wide...
- Objection!</i>

01:26:54.900 --> 01:26:58.222
Objection sustained.

01:27:02.940 --> 01:27:07.229
<i>Why did you leave
with Idgie Threadgoode that day?</i>

01:27:09.940 --> 01:27:12.261
<i>Answer the question, Mrs. Bennett.</i>

01:27:13.380 --> 01:27:15.303
Because she...

01:27:18.980 --> 01:27:21.904
...she's the best friend I ever had.

01:27:22.020 --> 01:27:24.148
And I love her.

01:27:25.260 --> 01:27:27.501
<i>Thank you, Mrs. Bennett. That will be all.</i>

01:27:27.620 --> 01:27:33.263
<i>The defence calls as its last witness
the Reverend Herbert Scroggins.</i>

01:27:34.380 --> 01:27:37.224
Place your right hand on the Bible,
please, Reverend.

01:27:37.340 --> 01:27:39.263
I brought my own, if you don't mind.

01:27:40.980 --> 01:27:44.382
Do you swear to tell the whole truth
and nothing but the truth?

01:27:44.500 --> 01:27:46.423
I do.

01:27:48.340 --> 01:27:54.427
<i>Do you have information about the whereabouts
of Idgie Threadgoode and her coloured man,</i>

01:27:54.540 --> 01:27:59.546
known as Big George,
on the night of September 30th, 1933?

01:27:59.660 --> 01:28:01.583
Yes, sir, I do.

01:28:01.700 --> 01:28:06.342
<i>It has been suggested here that she and
her coloured man were at her mother's house.</i>

01:28:06.460 --> 01:28:08.383
<i>Can you confirm that?</i>

01:28:08.500 --> 01:28:11.390
No, sir. That is a lie.

01:28:11.500 --> 01:28:14.106
Shit.

01:28:14.220 --> 01:28:20.148
<i>It has been my habit to write down all the dates
of the activities of the church in my Bible.</i>

01:28:20.260 --> 01:28:24.709
<i>And I've shown that
the night of September 30th, 1933</i>

01:28:24.820 --> 01:28:29.223
was the start of our annual revival
down at the Baptist camp ground.

01:28:30.340 --> 01:28:32.468
Sister Threadgoode was there,

01:28:32.580 --> 01:28:36.380
<i>along with her hired man George Pullman,</i>

01:28:36.500 --> 01:28:38.423
who was in charge of the barbecue,

01:28:38.540 --> 01:28:40.429
just as he has been every year

01:28:40.540 --> 01:28:43.066
<i>- for the last ten years.
- Objection!</i>

01:28:43.180 --> 01:28:47.469
That doesn't mean anything. The murder could
have taken place any time in the next few days.

01:28:47.580 --> 01:28:50.026
Have you ever been to one of our revivals, sir?

01:28:50.140 --> 01:28:52.063
<i>Well, no.</i>

01:28:52.180 --> 01:28:54.421
Do you attend church regularly, sir?

01:28:54.540 --> 01:28:56.588
Of course I do.

01:28:56.700 --> 01:29:03.345
<i>Good. Well, maybe if you attended one of
our revivals, you'd know they last three days</i>

01:29:03.460 --> 01:29:05.667
and three nights. Your Honour.

01:29:07.860 --> 01:29:10.670
<i>Approach the bench.</i>

01:29:11.780 --> 01:29:15.023
Percy, it don't look like you've got a case at all.

01:29:15.140 --> 01:29:17.063
In the first place, there's no body.

01:29:17.180 --> 01:29:20.104
Second, we've got us a preacher
nobody's going to dispute.

01:29:20.220 --> 01:29:21.949
But, Your Honour...

01:29:22.060 --> 01:29:25.064
I'm telling you what you've got
is a whole lot of nothing.

01:29:26.180 --> 01:29:28.308
<i>I say Frank Bennett got himself drunk,</i>

01:29:28.420 --> 01:29:32.311
<i>drove into the river and was long ago eaten up.</i>

01:29:32.420 --> 01:29:34.548
And I don't give a good goddamn!

01:29:35.660 --> 01:29:38.311
What we got us here
is a case of accidental death.

01:29:38.420 --> 01:29:40.422
Case dismissed!

01:29:49.380 --> 01:29:51.303
See you in church, sister?

01:29:52.420 --> 01:29:54.343
Reverend.

01:29:55.460 --> 01:29:57.986
I can't believe he actually swore on the Bible.

01:29:59.100 --> 01:30:01.023
Well, not really.

01:30:01.140 --> 01:30:05.862
If that judge had looked any closer, he'd have
seen it was really a copy of Moby Dick.

01:30:08.020 --> 01:30:09.943
But why did he do it?

01:30:10.060 --> 01:30:15.191
For the sheer joy of seeing you in church again,
which I suggested to him might be your penance.

01:30:15.300 --> 01:30:17.746
- You didn't promise him?
- Yes, ma'am, I did.

01:30:17.860 --> 01:30:19.783
And I never break my word.

01:30:19.900 --> 01:30:23.222
If I live a thousand years,
I will never forgive you for this.

01:30:23.340 --> 01:30:25.991
I don't know what's worse, church or jail.

01:30:28.500 --> 01:30:31.026
Towanda!

01:30:52.780 --> 01:30:55.989
Evelyn... what in the hell are you doing?

01:30:56.100 --> 01:30:58.023
I need some light and air.

01:30:59.140 --> 01:31:03.782
Why don't you step outside and take one of
your walks or your jogs or whatever it is you do?

01:31:05.860 --> 01:31:07.783
And there's no dinner, either!

01:31:07.900 --> 01:31:09.186
Ed,

01:31:09.300 --> 01:31:12.622
do you have any idea
why I've been going to all these classes?

01:31:12.740 --> 01:31:15.346
<i>- No.</i>
- I've been trying to save our marriage.

01:31:15.460 --> 01:31:19.909
What's the point of my trying if you're gonna
just sit on your butt drinking beer

01:31:20.020 --> 01:31:21.943
and watching baseball...

01:31:22.060 --> 01:31:23.983
basketball...

01:31:24.100 --> 01:31:26.023
football...

01:31:26.140 --> 01:31:28.871
bowling and hockey and golf and...

01:31:29.940 --> 01:31:31.863
...Challenge of the Gladiators?

01:31:38.060 --> 01:31:39.983
Mrs. Couch?

01:31:40.100 --> 01:31:42.341
I'm Sue, Mrs. Otis's daughter-in-law.

01:31:42.460 --> 01:31:45.703
How are you? I've heard so much about you
from Mrs. Threadgoode.

01:31:45.820 --> 01:31:49.347
She is so sweet. She's been looking after
my mother-in-law for years.

01:31:49.460 --> 01:31:52.066
Well, now, how is Mrs. Otis doing, by the way?

01:31:52.180 --> 01:31:56.390
Much better, thank you. I guess it just takes time
getting used to a strange place.

01:31:56.500 --> 01:32:00.346
Glad to hear it. I know Mrs. Threadgoode's been
anxious to get home for some time.

01:32:00.460 --> 01:32:04.431
Mrs. Couch, Mrs. Threadgoode
doesn't have a house any more.

01:32:04.540 --> 01:32:06.463
They tore that down.

01:32:06.580 --> 01:32:09.231
- What?
- Well, they had to. It was falling apart.

01:32:09.340 --> 01:32:11.263
And it was condemned.

01:32:11.380 --> 01:32:13.303
Oh, no.

01:32:14.420 --> 01:32:16.343
Does she know that?

01:32:16.460 --> 01:32:19.111
<i>No, well, we didn't see any point in telling her.</i>

01:32:19.220 --> 01:32:21.427
<i>It would just break her heart, poor old thing.</i>

01:32:22.540 --> 01:32:25.225
But I am so glad I got a chance to meet you.

01:32:25.340 --> 01:32:27.468
You take care of yourself, now. Bye-bye.

01:33:35.740 --> 01:33:37.663
Evelyn, hey.

01:33:37.780 --> 01:33:39.509
<i>Hey...</i>

01:33:39.620 --> 01:33:41.543
Do you like my roses?

01:33:42.620 --> 01:33:48.070
Since I can't get home to look at my own roses,
I made myself a paper garden.

01:33:48.180 --> 01:33:51.423
<i>- I've got everything but the bugs.
- They're lovely.</i>

01:33:51.540 --> 01:33:53.941
- Have you been here long?
- Happy birthday.

01:33:55.060 --> 01:33:56.983
I shouldn't have woken you up.

01:33:57.100 --> 01:34:01.230
Of course you should. Don't you never
let me sleep through a visitors' day, honey.

01:34:01.340 --> 01:34:03.263
I look forward to them all week.

01:34:03.380 --> 01:34:05.303
So do I, Mrs. Threadgoode. So do I.

01:34:06.420 --> 01:34:11.665
Oh, I can't believe you remembered!
You made me fried green tomatoes!

01:34:15.460 --> 01:34:17.383
They're delicious!

01:34:17.500 --> 01:34:19.423
It's your recipe. Are they cold?

01:34:19.540 --> 01:34:20.826
No.

01:34:20.940 --> 01:34:24.990
They're just the way we used to have them
at the Whistle Stop Café.

01:34:25.100 --> 01:34:28.786
You couldn't be sweeter to me
if you were my own daughter.

01:34:28.900 --> 01:34:30.823
Here's your napkin.

01:34:30.940 --> 01:34:32.863
Wait, wait, wait.

01:34:32.980 --> 01:34:34.903
Queen!

01:34:37.980 --> 01:34:39.903
You know,

01:34:40.020 --> 01:34:41.943
I don't feel 83.

01:34:42.060 --> 01:34:44.188
It son of slipped up on me.

01:34:48.660 --> 01:34:50.867
I never expected to live this long.

01:34:51.980 --> 01:34:54.904
Of course, the Lord takes us home
when he wants us.

01:35:05.180 --> 01:35:07.103
Are you all right?

01:35:09.500 --> 01:35:11.707
I was thinking about Ruth.

01:35:13.740 --> 01:35:16.664
After the trial was over,
everything went back to normal.

01:35:16.780 --> 01:35:20.182
<i>Till that fall when Ruth lost her appetite.</i>

01:35:20.300 --> 01:35:22.906
<i>By the time Dr. Hadley looked at her,</i>

01:35:23.020 --> 01:35:26.263
<i>he said the cancer was so bad
she only had a couple of weeks.</i>

01:35:27.380 --> 01:35:29.667
<i>We moved her to the Threadgoode house</i>

01:35:29.780 --> 01:35:32.784
<i>and put her downstairs
so she'd be more comfortable.</i>

01:35:34.460 --> 01:35:37.703
<i>Sipsey moved in with her and never left her side.</i>

01:35:40.980 --> 01:35:44.029
<i>Idgie just prayed for a miracle.</i>

01:36:03.980 --> 01:36:05.903
Now, listen to me.

01:36:07.380 --> 01:36:09.701
Make sure he graduates.

01:36:09.820 --> 01:36:11.743
And don't...

01:36:11.860 --> 01:36:16.422
let him come to the funeral.
I don't want him going through that mess.

01:36:16.540 --> 01:36:18.463
Would you quit talking like that?

01:36:18.580 --> 01:36:20.503
What funeral?

01:36:20.620 --> 01:36:24.466
You're gonna be back on your feet again
and just fine

01:36:24.580 --> 01:36:26.503
<i>in just a few days.</i>

01:36:26.620 --> 01:36:28.543
<i>Just you wait.</i>

01:36:31.060 --> 01:36:33.028
What's the matter, son?

01:36:38.580 --> 01:36:40.503
Let's go for a walk.

01:36:42.260 --> 01:36:44.342
<i>Did you get into a fight?</i>

01:36:44.460 --> 01:36:46.383
I got punched in the nose.

01:36:46.500 --> 01:36:48.423
I can't play like everyone else.

01:36:50.540 --> 01:36:53.384
Hey, did I ever tell you the story
about... the oysters?

01:36:53.500 --> 01:36:55.821
All the millions of them just lying around.

01:36:55.940 --> 01:36:58.591
And God puts sand in one of them
and makes a pearl.

01:36:58.700 --> 01:37:00.623
Oh.

01:37:02.180 --> 01:37:04.831
Did I ever tell you about Eva's three-legged dog?

01:37:04.940 --> 01:37:06.863
How it never felt sorry for itself,

01:37:06.980 --> 01:37:10.905
and howl ought to be smarter than a dumb dog
and not feel sorry for myself?

01:37:12.500 --> 01:37:14.741
You listen to everything I say, don't you?

01:37:15.860 --> 01:37:17.783
You get real mad at me when I don't.

01:37:22.300 --> 01:37:24.223
You know about your mama.

01:37:25.340 --> 01:37:27.263
She's sick.

01:37:27.380 --> 01:37:29.303
Mm-hm.

01:37:31.780 --> 01:37:33.942
You see, now is the time for courage.

01:37:35.060 --> 01:37:36.983
I guess you already know that...

01:37:38.700 --> 01:37:43.627
...there are angels masquerading as people
walking round, and your mom is the bravest one.

01:37:48.860 --> 01:37:50.783
Come here.

01:37:57.700 --> 01:38:00.226
Mommy, I can hit! You should see me!

01:38:00.340 --> 01:38:05.346
Aunt Idgie, she hit me in the back with
a curve ball. I didn't duck and I hardly cried.

01:38:05.460 --> 01:38:07.383
She hit you?

01:38:10.140 --> 01:38:14.190
She did that to me once, too, but...
I think I did cry.

01:38:17.220 --> 01:38:18.984
<i>Mama?</i>

01:38:19.100 --> 01:38:21.023
I'm sorry if you're sad.

01:38:22.140 --> 01:38:26.350
Well, give me a big kiss, then,
and I'll never be sad again.

01:38:33.580 --> 01:38:35.503
And you best not be sad neither.

01:38:35.620 --> 01:38:37.304
You understand?

01:38:38.820 --> 01:38:40.743
You promise?

01:38:41.860 --> 01:38:43.385
Promise.

01:38:43.500 --> 01:38:45.229
Attaboy.

01:38:45.340 --> 01:38:47.263
You can go and wash up.

01:39:10.140 --> 01:39:12.063
Sweet baby.

01:39:15.580 --> 01:39:17.503
You two be alone now.

01:39:19.740 --> 01:39:20.946
Hey, girl.

01:39:25.100 --> 01:39:27.023
No.

01:39:29.460 --> 01:39:31.383
That's nice.

01:39:34.380 --> 01:39:36.303
Will you do one thing for me?

01:39:36.420 --> 01:39:38.343
Yeah, anything.

01:39:38.460 --> 01:39:40.428
Be good to yourself.

01:39:40.540 --> 01:39:42.463
Even...

01:39:43.540 --> 01:39:48.421
...settle down if you can find someone
who can beat you in poker.

01:39:56.060 --> 01:39:58.984
There are so many things I wanna say to you.

01:40:00.700 --> 01:40:02.623
No.

01:40:03.740 --> 01:40:05.663
I love your stories.

01:40:06.780 --> 01:40:09.351
Tell me a story, Idgie.

01:40:15.700 --> 01:40:17.623
<i>Go on, you old bee charmer.</i>

01:40:18.740 --> 01:40:20.868
<i>Tell me a good tall tale.</i>

01:40:23.780 --> 01:40:26.101
Tell me the one about the lake.

01:40:27.700 --> 01:40:29.623
What lake?

01:40:29.740 --> 01:40:33.028
The one that used to be here.

01:40:38.660 --> 01:40:40.583
Well, that was just a lie.

01:40:42.420 --> 01:40:44.343
I know that, fool.

01:40:44.460 --> 01:40:47.031
Tell me anyway.

01:40:48.140 --> 01:40:50.063
Tell me a story.

01:40:56.980 --> 01:40:58.903
One time...

01:40:59.020 --> 01:41:00.943
there was this lake.

01:41:06.740 --> 01:41:09.061
And it was right outside of town.

01:41:11.180 --> 01:41:14.787
We used to go fishing and swimming
and canoeing in it.

01:41:17.700 --> 01:41:23.150
See, one November, this big flock of ducks
came in and landed on that lake.

01:41:25.460 --> 01:41:29.784
And then the temperature dropped so fast
that the lake just froze right there.

01:41:30.860 --> 01:41:32.385
And they er...

01:41:32.500 --> 01:41:35.231
The ducks... they...

01:41:36.980 --> 01:41:39.824
...flew off, you see,
and they took that lake with them.

01:41:44.180 --> 01:41:47.024
Now they say that lake is
somewhere over in Georgia.

01:41:48.380 --> 01:41:50.303
Can you imagine?

01:42:46.660 --> 01:42:48.583
It's all right, honey.

01:42:49.700 --> 01:42:51.623
Let her go.

01:42:51.740 --> 01:42:53.663
Let her go.

01:42:56.380 --> 01:42:58.303
You know, Miss Ruth was a lady.

01:43:00.260 --> 01:43:04.504
And a lady always knows when to leave.

01:43:12.140 --> 01:43:15.781
<i>When I think on our departed sister
Ruth Jamison,</i>

01:43:15.900 --> 01:43:18.824
<i>I'm reminded of our Lord's
Sermon on the Mount.</i>

01:43:19.940 --> 01:43:23.990
<i>It's funny how strong
Ruth affected everyone.</i>

01:43:25.100 --> 01:43:27.023
<i>Even Smokey Lonesome.</i>

01:43:28.940 --> 01:43:30.863
<i>When he died a few years back,</i>

01:43:30.980 --> 01:43:32.903
<i>he had one possession on him.</i>

01:43:34.300 --> 01:43:36.223
<i>A picture of Ruth.</i>

01:43:38.100 --> 01:43:40.580
<i>He was in love with her
from the first time he saw her.</i>

01:43:41.700 --> 01:43:43.862
<i>We all were.</i>

01:43:50.460 --> 01:43:52.940
I shouldn't have told you this.

01:43:54.060 --> 01:43:55.585
I hate death.

01:43:56.660 --> 01:43:58.583
It scares me so.

01:43:58.700 --> 01:44:00.623
Death is nothing to be afraid of.

01:44:00.740 --> 01:44:04.062
Look at me, I'm at the jumping-off place,
and I ain't afraid one bit.

01:44:06.500 --> 01:44:08.502
Oh, Ninny.

01:44:08.620 --> 01:44:10.861
You're so brave.

01:44:12.660 --> 01:44:14.583
Ruth and Idgie were brave, not me.

01:44:16.300 --> 01:44:18.507
I wouldn't be afraid of death if I was you.

01:44:19.580 --> 01:44:21.821
I'd be more afraid of driving

01:44:21.940 --> 01:44:23.863
<i>in rush-hour traffic.</i>

01:44:43.860 --> 01:44:45.783
Hi, honey.

01:44:45.900 --> 01:44:47.823
Look what I got you.

01:44:48.940 --> 01:44:50.863
Ed!

01:44:50.980 --> 01:44:52.903
How sweet!

01:44:53.020 --> 01:44:54.943
Lilies. My favourite.

01:44:55.060 --> 01:44:57.950
I know. Sometimes I even amaze myself.

01:44:58.060 --> 01:44:59.983
What's the occasion?

01:45:00.100 --> 01:45:02.023
Honey, I just...

01:45:02.140 --> 01:45:04.666
feel sorry about the past few months, you know.

01:45:04.780 --> 01:45:06.782
I don't know what you're really up to,

01:45:06.900 --> 01:45:08.823
what's going on with you, but...

01:45:08.940 --> 01:45:12.661
I guess I could have been more helpful
with your job and everything.

01:45:13.780 --> 01:45:15.703
Well, why are you er...

01:45:15.820 --> 01:45:19.347
Why are you putting up this wall
where you just tore one down?

01:45:19.460 --> 01:45:22.304
Well... I changed my mind.

01:45:22.420 --> 01:45:26.345
Well, I don't mean to seem dense or anything,
but what's changed?

01:45:26.460 --> 01:45:28.383
The air and the light.

01:45:31.220 --> 01:45:33.143
Ed...

01:45:34.260 --> 01:45:38.504
You remember how you used to tell me
you always wanted two women in your house?

01:45:38.620 --> 01:45:40.543
Oh, God.

01:45:40.660 --> 01:45:42.185
Yeah.

01:45:43.260 --> 01:45:45.183
Well...

01:45:45.300 --> 01:45:47.906
what if I was the younger of the two?

01:45:48.020 --> 01:45:49.909
I don't believe I get your drift.

01:45:51.020 --> 01:45:54.422
I want something more than
I've ever wanted anything before.

01:45:55.820 --> 01:45:59.142
I want to bring Mrs. Threadgoode to our home.

01:46:00.460 --> 01:46:02.383
I want her to live here with us.

01:46:03.500 --> 01:46:05.707
I want to give her the love she's given me.

01:46:05.820 --> 01:46:07.743
You're kidding me, aren't you?

01:46:07.860 --> 01:46:09.783
I'm absolutely serious.

01:46:09.900 --> 01:46:12.904
That's why I'm putting the wall
to Kyle's room back up.

01:46:14.020 --> 01:46:15.943
Well, honey...

01:46:16.060 --> 01:46:18.506
this isn't something you're just gonna do.

01:46:18.620 --> 01:46:23.262
She's an old woman. What if she got sick
or something? Who's gonna take care of her?

01:46:23.380 --> 01:46:24.905
I will.

01:46:25.020 --> 01:46:26.943
I can't leave her in that place.

01:46:27.060 --> 01:46:30.587
She's not a stray cat or something.
Hell, she isn't even family.

01:46:30.700 --> 01:46:32.623
- She's family to me.
- Now, Evelyn.

01:46:33.740 --> 01:46:35.663
<i>Evelyn...</i>

01:46:36.740 --> 01:46:38.663
<i>Honey...</i>

01:46:39.740 --> 01:46:40.662
<i>Er... look...</i>

01:46:41.740 --> 01:46:45.586
Have you mentioned
this harebrained idea of yours to her?

01:46:45.700 --> 01:46:47.828
- Not yet.
- Well, good!

01:46:47.940 --> 01:46:50.864
Then we'll just pretend it never happened.

01:46:50.980 --> 01:46:53.904
I'm making my own money now.
I'll pay for everything.

01:46:54.020 --> 01:46:55.943
You don't have to do a thing.

01:46:57.060 --> 01:46:58.983
Evelyn...

01:47:00.100 --> 01:47:02.023
...it's never gonna happen.

01:47:02.140 --> 01:47:04.063
So just forget about it.

01:47:06.220 --> 01:47:08.143
Don't you ever say never to me.

01:47:17.340 --> 01:47:20.071
Someone helped put a mirror up
in front of my face.

01:47:20.180 --> 01:47:22.103
And I didn't like what I saw one bit.

01:47:22.220 --> 01:47:24.143
And you know what I did?

01:47:24.260 --> 01:47:25.785
I changed.

01:47:26.900 --> 01:47:29.551
And that someone was Mrs. Threadgoode.

01:47:29.660 --> 01:47:33.426
She needs my love and care now.
And I'm gonna give it to her.

01:47:36.580 --> 01:47:39.026
Now, if you'll excuse me, I have to go to the gym.

01:47:45.860 --> 01:47:47.783
And if you won't listen to reason,

01:47:47.900 --> 01:47:49.823
there's always Towanda.

01:48:04.580 --> 01:48:06.503
Hey, Nin...

01:48:10.900 --> 01:48:12.823
What are you doing?

01:48:12.940 --> 01:48:14.863
Those are her things.

01:48:14.980 --> 01:48:17.904
What are you doing in here?
Where is Mrs. Threadgoode?

01:48:18.020 --> 01:48:19.351
Who?

01:48:19.460 --> 01:48:22.225
Mrs. Threadgoode, the woman who lives here.
Are you deaf?

01:48:22.340 --> 01:48:27.471
I'm sorry, miss. All they told me was that
the woman who lived in here died this morning.

01:48:30.220 --> 01:48:32.143
Oh, my God.

01:48:32.260 --> 01:48:34.183
What...

01:48:35.300 --> 01:48:37.223
What are you saying?

01:48:37.340 --> 01:48:39.263
<i>Well, she died early this morning.</i>

01:48:39.380 --> 01:48:44.181
<i>They were short-handed, so they asked me
to take all this stuff down. That's all I know.</i>

01:49:03.940 --> 01:49:05.863
Stop!

01:49:05.980 --> 01:49:07.903
What is the matter with you people?

01:49:09.020 --> 01:49:11.626
Can't you wait a goddamn day, for Christ's sake?

01:49:11.740 --> 01:49:14.710
Do you have no respect? These are her things!

01:49:14.820 --> 01:49:18.745
I'm sorry, miss, but they told me
to get this room ready for another patient.

01:49:18.860 --> 01:49:22.182
She may be just another patient to you,
but she was my friend.

01:49:22.300 --> 01:49:24.223
And I loved her.

01:49:24.340 --> 01:49:25.830
Sorry.

01:49:25.940 --> 01:49:27.863
I'm just following orders.

01:49:27.980 --> 01:49:29.550
What is going on here?

01:49:29.660 --> 01:49:32.584
Why didn't you call me?
You could have at least called me.

01:49:32.700 --> 01:49:36.750
Sorry, Mrs. Couch. It just never occurred to me
that you would take it this hard.

01:49:36.860 --> 01:49:40.182
- I didn't even get to tell her goodbye.
- I know.

01:49:40.300 --> 01:49:43.941
These things are difficult.
But she died peacefully in her sleep.

01:49:44.060 --> 01:49:47.223
To tell the truth,
I thought you'd be happy for Mrs. Threadgoode.

01:49:47.340 --> 01:49:49.741
- Happy?
- Why, yes. This is what she wanted.

01:49:49.860 --> 01:49:51.783
What, to be dead?!

01:49:51.900 --> 01:49:53.823
No, to go home. You just missed her.

01:49:53.940 --> 01:49:56.181
She left in a yellow cab about a half-hour ago.

01:49:57.260 --> 01:49:59.661
I don't understand. What, a cab?

01:49:59.780 --> 01:50:03.830
She said there wasn't no reason for her to stay
now that Mrs. Otis had died.

01:50:03.940 --> 01:50:05.863
Mrs...

01:50:05.980 --> 01:50:08.586
Otis is dead?

01:50:09.700 --> 01:50:11.623
Oh, Mrs. Otis died.

01:50:11.740 --> 01:50:13.663
Mrs. Otis died!

01:50:13.780 --> 01:50:15.703
Mrs. Otis!

01:50:15.820 --> 01:50:17.743
Mrs...!

01:50:17.860 --> 01:50:20.511
Not that I'm glad that Mrs. Otis died, it's just...

01:50:21.620 --> 01:50:23.861
Oh, God, I've got to stop her.

01:51:00.980 --> 01:51:02.903
Hey, Evelyn.

01:51:03.020 --> 01:51:04.943
Somebody stole my house.

01:51:05.060 --> 01:51:06.983
It was right here when I left.

01:51:07.100 --> 01:51:09.023
Unless...

01:51:09.140 --> 01:51:12.428
Oh, Evelyn, you don't reckon I'm crazy, do you?

01:51:12.540 --> 01:51:14.463
It was here when I left.

01:51:14.580 --> 01:51:16.503
No, honey, you're not crazy.

01:51:16.620 --> 01:51:18.543
This is the place.

01:51:18.660 --> 01:51:21.709
Well, why would anyone
want to steal an old lady's home?

01:51:23.260 --> 01:51:25.183
It wasn't worth nothing.

01:51:25.300 --> 01:51:27.826
Oh, honey. Nobody stole it.

01:51:27.940 --> 01:51:29.863
They had to tear it down.

01:51:29.980 --> 01:51:31.903
It was condemned.

01:51:32.020 --> 01:51:34.466
I'm sorry. I should have told you.

01:51:34.580 --> 01:51:36.901
Somebody should have told me.

01:51:37.020 --> 01:51:39.341
I'm old. I'm not a child.

01:51:39.460 --> 01:51:41.383
I'm sorry.

01:51:42.700 --> 01:51:46.944
My husband Cleo and I lived in this house
for more than 40 years.

01:51:48.060 --> 01:51:49.983
Now it's gone.

01:51:51.540 --> 01:51:53.463
83 years' worth of living.

01:51:53.580 --> 01:51:56.026
And all that's left of me is what's in this box.

01:51:56.140 --> 01:51:58.905
A bunch of old cards and pictures.

01:51:59.020 --> 01:52:00.943
Come on. I'll take you home.

01:52:01.060 --> 01:52:02.983
This is my home!

01:52:03.100 --> 01:52:05.023
And now it's gone.

01:52:05.140 --> 01:52:07.063
And Mrs. Otis has gone.

01:52:10.100 --> 01:52:12.023
I don't quite know what to do.

01:52:12.140 --> 01:52:16.065
It's the first time I can remember
when I don't have a soul to look after.

01:52:16.180 --> 01:52:18.626
You can come look after me and Ed.

01:52:19.740 --> 01:52:23.631
You're sweet,
but I think you're doing just fine on your own.

01:52:23.740 --> 01:52:26.346
Don't you know you'd be like a gift for us?

01:52:27.460 --> 01:52:29.667
You're the reason I get up every morning!

01:52:30.780 --> 01:52:33.101
And that Mary Kay's having such a good year.

01:52:34.300 --> 01:52:37.702
And that I don't look like
some blob from a horror movie.

01:52:38.820 --> 01:52:41.221
Well, with a little help from Idgie and Ruth.

01:52:41.340 --> 01:52:43.422
Come on.

01:52:43.540 --> 01:52:45.463
I've got your room all ready.

01:52:46.580 --> 01:52:48.867
What does Ed say about all this?

01:52:48.980 --> 01:52:50.903
He'll learn to love it.

01:52:55.940 --> 01:52:59.865
Did I ever tell you
that Mrs. Otis was Sipsey's baby sister?

01:52:59.980 --> 01:53:01.903
- No, ma'am.
- Yes, she was.

01:53:02.020 --> 01:53:05.308
Mrs. Otis was with Sipsey and me
the night Sipsey died.

01:53:06.420 --> 01:53:11.347
Sipsey told me a story that night
I've never told a living soul, Evelyn.

01:53:11.460 --> 01:53:16.705
<i>The story about what really happened
the night Frank Bennett disappeared.</i>

01:53:53.060 --> 01:53:54.983
The show's hardly begun.

01:53:55.100 --> 01:53:57.182
You've got to come quick now, you hear me?

01:54:05.420 --> 01:54:07.104
Never mind.

01:54:25.100 --> 01:54:26.625
Excuse me, sir.

01:54:27.740 --> 01:54:30.346
I don't believe you should be going anywhere

01:54:30.460 --> 01:54:32.064
with Ruth's baby.

01:54:42.380 --> 01:54:47.022
<i>- Like I said, you ain't going nowhere.</i>
- Damn, you're a thick-headed son of a bitch,

01:54:47.140 --> 01:54:48.266
ain't you?

01:54:54.380 --> 01:54:57.509
I told you you ain't going nowheres
with Miss Ruth's baby.

01:55:04.140 --> 01:55:06.063
Come on, angel. Come on.

01:55:06.180 --> 01:55:08.103
Come on, sweetheart.

01:55:08.220 --> 01:55:10.143
It's all right.

01:55:10.260 --> 01:55:12.308
It's all right, baby.

01:55:15.100 --> 01:55:17.706
<i>It was self-defence.</i>

01:55:18.820 --> 01:55:21.824
<i>I don't know why any white jury
would care why] did it.</i>

01:55:21.940 --> 01:55:25.149
- I saw it and I can testi...
- Excuse me, here.

01:55:25.260 --> 01:55:27.183
I don't mean no offence here,

01:55:27.300 --> 01:55:30.349
but I don't know who is less likely
to convince the jury,

01:55:30.460 --> 01:55:32.542
my mama or Mr. Smokey here.

01:55:33.660 --> 01:55:35.264
No offence taken.

01:55:35.380 --> 01:55:37.667
You're a good man, Mr. Smokey.

01:55:37.780 --> 01:55:40.511
- You did good.
- The sun's almost up.

01:55:44.180 --> 01:55:46.103
George...

01:55:48.740 --> 01:55:50.663
I think...

01:55:50.780 --> 01:55:52.703
it's hog-boiling time.

01:55:54.060 --> 01:55:55.983
No, ma'am. It ain't cold enough.

01:55:56.100 --> 01:55:58.023
It's hog-boiling time.

01:56:02.100 --> 01:56:04.023
<i>Hey, George...</i>

01:56:05.140 --> 01:56:07.268
...when is that barbecue gonna be ready?

01:56:07.380 --> 01:56:09.303
It's gonna be ready any time now.

01:56:09.420 --> 01:56:12.344
It smells so damn good
I just can't wait to get me some.

01:56:13.860 --> 01:56:16.591
Now, don't you forget to call me
when that's ready.

01:56:16.700 --> 01:56:18.623
All right.

01:56:30.380 --> 01:56:32.303
Here you go.

01:56:34.420 --> 01:56:36.343
Miss Idgie.

01:56:36.460 --> 01:56:38.667
Smokey left town.

01:56:38.780 --> 01:56:41.021
I thought it'd be best under the circumstances.

01:56:42.340 --> 01:56:44.866
He asked that you tell Ruth goodbye.

01:56:45.980 --> 01:56:47.903
Shame he had to go.

01:57:01.100 --> 01:57:03.341
This is about the best barbecue I ever ate!

01:57:04.860 --> 01:57:06.988
The secret's in the sauce.

01:57:16.460 --> 01:57:18.383
Sipsey?

01:57:18.500 --> 01:57:20.423
My God.

01:57:20.540 --> 01:57:23.464
That frying pan did more
than fry chicken that night.

01:57:26.180 --> 01:57:28.421
Did Idgie really barbecue Frank Bennett?

01:57:28.540 --> 01:57:30.463
Oh, you're pulling my leg!

01:57:30.580 --> 01:57:33.106
The secret's in the sauce, or so I've been told.

01:57:37.300 --> 01:57:40.270
Now you know why Idgie had to go on trial.

01:57:41.340 --> 01:57:43.946
She knew the law would never believe Sipsey.
No!

01:57:44.060 --> 01:57:49.191
Sipsey or Big George or anyone else of colour
would have been hanging from the nearest tree.

01:57:50.300 --> 01:57:54.100
To this day,
I'm still not sure whether Ruth ever believed

01:57:54.220 --> 01:57:57.144
that Idgie didn't kill Frank Bennett.

01:57:59.260 --> 01:58:01.183
Truth's a funny thing sometimes.

01:58:03.300 --> 01:58:05.223
I feel better now.

01:58:05.340 --> 01:58:07.263
Good.

01:58:07.380 --> 01:58:12.102
I feel better because all these people will live
as long as you remember them.

01:58:13.220 --> 01:58:15.143
You reminded me...

01:58:15.260 --> 01:58:17.991
about what the most important thing in life is.

01:58:18.100 --> 01:58:20.421
- Do you know what I think it is?
- No, ma'am.

01:58:20.540 --> 01:58:22.463
Friends.

01:58:22.580 --> 01:58:24.503
Best friends.

01:58:24.620 --> 01:58:26.543
Oh, Ninny.

01:58:28.180 --> 01:58:30.103
Look.

01:58:33.980 --> 01:58:35.903
Oh.

01:58:55.060 --> 01:58:57.222
Idgie?

01:59:00.260 --> 01:59:02.183
Idgie's alive?

01:59:02.300 --> 01:59:04.223
<i>Oh, yes.</i>

01:59:04.340 --> 01:59:07.662
She's still out and about,
charming bees and selling honey.

01:59:07.780 --> 01:59:09.828
Sometimes I think I catch a glimpse of her.

01:59:18.340 --> 01:59:20.263
Maybe we'll see her today.

01:59:20.380 --> 01:59:21.870
Maybe.

01:59:23.980 --> 01:59:25.630
Let's go.

01:59:38.340 --> 01:59:41.344
<i>After Ruth died and the rail road stopped running,</i>

01:59:42.420 --> 01:59:46.266
<i>the café shut down
and everybody just scattered to the winds.</i>

01:59:47.380 --> 01:59:50.429
<i>It was never more
than just a little knockabout place.</i>

01:59:50.540 --> 01:59:52.463
<i>But now that I look back on it,</i>

01:59:53.580 --> 01:59:55.503
<i>when that café closed,</i>

01:59:55.620 --> 01:59:58.021
<i>the heart of the town just stopped beating.</i>

01:59:59.540 --> 02:00:04.831
<i>It's funny how a little place like this
brought so many people together.</i>

